FALSE-COMPLETION failure mode (gm method): a chain can reach COMPLETE with the deliverable NOT actually done when (a) the plan contains self-cancelling re-plans -- a row does X, a later row reverts X, a third redoes X -- each row honestly status:completed, so the gate sees all-rows-done while the real deliverable oscillates do->revert->redo and never converges; and (b) witness_evidence is NARRATIVE (a claimed 'diff -> exit 0' or 'executed prior turn') rather than captured exec output, which the gate stores as a non-empty string without verifying. The gate is not broken in either case -- both are convergence/honesty failures upstream of it. Guard by: never re-cut a cover into a direction that undoes landed work without first reconciling why; and make witness_evidence real captured output (exec/codesearch/browser), never a claim.